 30 AM - 2:00 PM    This workshop covers:Legal Research - Master Westlaw/L
 exisNexis and legal search strategies  Legal Writing - Learn IRAC methodo
 logy and legal memo drafting  Case Analysis - Develop case briefing and s
 ynthesis skills  Professional Skills - Presentation training and cross-cu
 ltural legal discourse    Why This Program?Build law-school level skillsl
 ike legal research\, case analysis and legal writing and writingHave a cr
 oss-cultural and global experiencecollaborating with international studen
 ts from PeruGet ahead for law schoolby showing law schools your commitmen
 t and readiness!  Enrollment OptionsOption 1: For CreditCourse: B504 Intr
 oduction to Law: Legal Writing (3 credits)  Tuition: Standard undergradua
 te rate ($1\,229.64 in-state\; $4\,018.56 out-of-state) + $300 programmin
 g/activities fee ($1\,529.64 in-state\; $4\,318.56 out-of-state)  Benefit
 : Official transcript credit\, potential application toward MLS program  
