SUMMARY:Strategic Thinking in U.S.-Africa Policy and Intelligence (w/ LUN
 CH)
DESCRIPTION:Event Description:  How do policymakers and intelligence offi
 cers navigate complex decisions in Africa and beyond?  Join Judd Devermon
 t (https://www.csis.org/people/judd-devermont)\, former National Intellig
 ence Officer for Africa and former Senior Director for African Affairs at
  the White House\, for a live\, scenario-driven session on strategy\, ris
 k\, and global policymaking.  Devermont spent over a decade in the intell
 igence community\, advised two administrations\, authored the U.S. Strate
 gy toward Sub-Saharan Africa\, and directed major initiatives shaping bil
 lions in infrastructure\, digital connectivity\, and energy investments.T
 his is not a lecture. You will work through a real-world scenario: Africa
 n states balancing relationships with the U.S. and China while managing d
 omestic political and development pressures.  You'll assess risk\, identi
 fy second- and third-order effects\, evaluate trade-offs\, and recommend 
 a course of action.What you'll gain:      Insight into how intelligence a
 nd policy intersect          Frameworks to anticipate unintended conseque
 nces          How analysis translates into real-world decisions          
 A window into careers in intelligence\, government\, and think tanks    L
 unch will be provided!&#160\;Come ready to debate\, analyze\, and defend 
 your conclusions in an interactive\, off-the-record setting.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p data-start="144" data-end="168"><strong d
 ata-start="144" data-end="166">Event Description:</strong></p><p data-sta
 rt="170" data-end="266">  How do policymakers and intelligence officers n
 avigate complex decisions in Africa and beyond?</p><p data-start="268" da
 ta-end="485">  Join <a href="https://www.csis.org/people/judd-devermont">
 Judd Devermont</a>\, former National Intelligence Officer for Africa and 
 former Senior Director for African Affairs at the White House\, for a liv
 e\, scenario-driven session on strategy\, risk\, and global policymaking.
 </p><p data-start="268" data-end="485"><img src="https://lawfare-assets-n
 ew.azureedge.net/assets/images/default-source/contributor-images/3902.jpg
 ?sfvrsn=cba0bcf9_0" alt="" loading="lazy"/></p><p data-start="487" data-e
 nd="745">  Devermont spent over a decade in the intelligence community\, 
 advised two administrations\, authored the U.S. Strategy toward Sub-Sahar
 an Africa\, and directed major initiatives shaping billions in infrastruc
 ture\, digital connectivity\, and energy investments.</p><p data-start="7
 47" data-end="771"><strong>This is not a lecture. You will work through a
  real-world scenario:</strong> African states balancing relationships wit
 h the U.S. and China while managing domestic political and development pr
 essures.</p><p data-start="945" data-end="1063">  You'll assess risk\, id
 entify second- and third-order effects\, evaluate trade-offs\, and recomm
 end a course of action.</p><p data-start="1065" data-end="1088"><strong d
 ata-start="1065" data-end="1086">What you'll gain:</strong></p><ul data-s
 tart="1089" data-end="1321"><li data-start="1089" data-end="1143"><p data
 -start="1091" data-end="1143">      Insight into how intelligence and pol
 icy intersect    </p></li><li data-start="1144" data-end="1196"><p data-s
 tart="1146" data-end="1196">      Frameworks to anticipate unintended con
 sequences    </p></li><li data-start="1197" data-end="1250"><p data-start
 ="1199" data-end="1250">      How analysis translates into real-world dec
 isions    </p></li><li data-start="1251" data-end="1321"><p data-start="1
 253" data-end="1321">      A window into careers in intelligence\, govern
 ment\, and think tanks    </p></li></ul><p data-start="1323" data-end="14
 50"><strong>Lunch will be provided!</strong>&#160\;Come ready to debate\,
  analyze\, and defend your conclusions in an interactive\, off-the-record
  setting.</p>
